# secretlint ignore — local mirror of CI's TruffleHog + gitleaks.
#
# `--secretlintignore .gitignore` already covers everything the repo
# excludes from git. This file is the small additional set of files
# whose committed content intentionally looks secret-shaped:
#
#   - `.env.example` is a template of placeholder values. The
#     `xxxxxxxx...` runs match Stripe / Clerk regex shapes by design so
#     readers see the real prefix. CI's TruffleHog runs `--only-verified`
#     and gitleaks uses an allowlist for templated values; the local
#     pre-commit hook gets the same posture via this ignore.
#
# Any *new* file added here MUST be reviewed by a human — secretlint is
# the local trust boundary and silent suppressions defeat the gate.

.env.example
